<br>
I'll post links for the basic sash/headband check list.<br>
the Sash and Headband can't be done unless you have Freeport/Qeynos faction (something human monks need not worry about).  If you're an Iksar monk, there is a whole other prior quests to gain faction so they can even approach Freeport/Qeynos to do the Sash and Headband.<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=60" target="top">Sash and Headband Component Checklist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Then the next step is for the Robe of the Lost circle<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=82" target="top">Walk Thru of the Robe of the Lost Circle Quest</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
1. Targin the Rock camp in Sol B.  He was green to Ravissantia, but the kicker is all the Kobold's agro, and it can get hairy, but he can be solo'ed if you have someone to take care of the dog problem.  Best bet..get a xp group for the Kobold's and tag along and then hit Targin when he pops.  They say its a sparatic spawn time, yet when I went there, I noticed he was up at approx the same time 3 nights in a row....and that was 2am cst.  Needless to say the 3rd time, Targin met an untimely death at the hands of my monk accompanied with her Druid hubby, Aluamian. Loot the<br>
Code of Zan Fi<br>
2. Raster of Guk in Lguk Live side in the Minotaur room. Monkly says the PH is a Elder Mino for Raster and sadly I didn't pay attention since boredom set in, and I just killed all Mino's as they popped, solo also.  Raster pops near the pot against the wall though and doesn't wander, so he is easy to spot.  This was an easy camp, mostly because I was ally with the live frogs, so they never once bothered me.  After 4hrs at this camp Raster popped and was green to me at 53. Loot the Idol of Zan Fi<br>
3. Brother Qwinn in S. Karana.  I found him near or close to Lake Rathe zone, wandering.  He is a more frequent spawn now, so easy to track or find.  Head to the Aviak city in S. Karana, he walks by there also.  Turn into him the Code of Zan Fi, plus the Purple Headband.  He returns to you the Needle of the Void.<br>
4. Brother Zephyl, is in the Rathe Mountains and I had a tracker with me for him. He also wanders around approx loc of  752, 161. Drakes are PH for him also in this general area. Turn into Brother Zephyl the Idol of Zan Fi and the Red Sash and it will earn you the Rare Robe Pattern. Combine in a sewing kit, his item; the rare robe pattern, a swatch of shadow silk and a scroll containing Jonathan's Whistling Warsong. A no fail combine results you in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2003" target="top">Robe of the Lost Circle</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Next step is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=83" target="top">Robe of the Whistling Fist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
This is where I am at currently with Ravi, so have no tips to offer from personal xp, since the KC pipe camp has been camped almost everytime I checked, and the Chardok pipe camp is a very rare spawn.  I do have my Book of Immortals though that is required for.....<br>
<br>
The Final Step is of course the last step<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/kibadachi_uk/monkepicquest.htm" target="top">The Celestial Fists</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Of course after this step, stare and drool at the pretty swirling circles..and Oooh and Aaah over your <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2699" target="top">Celestial Fists</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
And tips, or suggestions, or corrections, please post and let me know.  I'm only up to my Robe of Lost Circle, and will never claim to know it all...I'm a gimp monk, after all.<br>
